      "body": "The Lance format is a modern columnar storage format engineered for machine-learning workloads. Lance stores data in a versioned, chunk-oriented layout that enables random-access reads without deserialising an entire file. The REDACTED supports zero-copy Arrow integration and is the storage layer that underpins LanceDB. Because the REDACTED is optimised for both sequential scans and random lookups, it outperforms Parquet on many ML access patterns.",
